Class Block<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Block<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements in this block
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Block<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    A block has a capacity and holds a sequence of elements (in a circular array). Blocks are mutable. Null values are NOT allowed. The type Block supports: (1) the insertion of elements at both end points and also in a given position, provided the block is not full, and (2) the removal of elements at both end points and also in a given position, provided the block is not empty.
    Author:
    antonialopes (AED 16/17 @ FCUL-DI)
